This paper involves the application of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) on medical images for classification, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of machine learning algorithms such as SVM and VBM also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the study involves the use of neural networks for feature learning, which could fall under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. The use of automatic feature learning also suggests that it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the study involves the analysis of brain MRI images, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
